{
  "texts": [
    "More precisely, for a given sentence, we first collect all predicted start and end tokens.",
    "For each predicted start token w s, at position i we seek an end token w e at position j ≥ i with matching label and minimal distance to w s and assign it to w s as its end token.",
    "Finally, we discard predicted start/end tokens which have no matching end/start token.",
    "This slightly differs from the IOB format [58], as only start and end token of a sequence are tagged and all tokens in between (1) are classified just like tokens which are not part of any sequence.",
    "A comparison of both tagging schemes can be found in Table 2.p s,i = softmax(W s h i + b s) W s ∈ R |S|×d, b s ∈ R |S|(2)p e,i = softmax(W e h i + b e) W e ∈ R |S|×d, b e ∈ R |S|For each extracted slot-filler i with start/end tokens w s resp."
  ]
}